T|28 ·|0|The landing/overview screen of Mission Control. Appears as dashboard-home.md in the creator's own Briefings folder (screenshot 181510).
T|28 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|The default landing view when you open a workspace's Mission Control — a top-level overview that orients the owner before they dive into the Decision Queue. Where the Decision Queue is the action funnel ("the 7 things that need me"), the Dashboard/Home is the at-a-glance status of the whole operation.
T|Purp|1|
T|What|0|A morning overview: sy health, ag live, what was handled overnight, and a pointer into the Decision Queue.
T|What|1|Summary tiles likely pulling from across the app: pnd decisions, posts awaiting approval, tasks in rv, software items needing rv, inbox state, rv/consulting status.
T|What|2|Per-workspace, so it re-themes and re-scopes when you switch workspaces.
T|What|3|
T|Rela|0|Sits above the Command Center group; feeds the owner into Decision Queue (01), Task Board (02), and the an surfaces.
T|Rela|1|Conceptually the "home" that the global top bar's status indicators (sy healthy, ag live) summarize.
T|Rela|2|
T|Rela|3|Confidence: Inferred. This page is named in the creator's Briefings folder (dashboard-home.md) but was not shown as a dedicated UI screenshot, and "Dashboard"/"Home" was not consistently visible in the captured sidebars (most crops show the Command group starting at Decision Queue). Treat the layout above as ds intent, not confirmed UI.